OL,3,C'Motherhood penalty' fuels pension
OL,4,Cgender gap crisis
OL,6,FA Jersey mother says she lacks
OL,7,F"financial stability" as she can't
OL,8,Fafford to pay into her pension pot.
OL,10,FMaternity leave means many will either
OL,11,Fhalt working for a period, or
OL,12,Fpermanently, and stop paying in
OL,13,Faltogether, resulting in what has been
OL,14,Fcalled the 'Motherhood Penalty'.
OL,16,FITV News spoke with Clair Anderson, a
OL,17,FJersey mother of twins, who hasn't
OL,18,Fpaid into her pension since her
OL,19,Fchildren, turning 11 this year, were
OL,20,Fborn.
