OL,3,C'Motherhood penalty' fuels pension
OL,4,Cgender gap crisis
OL,6,FShe took five years off when the twins
OL,7,Farrived, with no income. She returned
OL,8,Fto part-time work in 2021 but says she
OL,9,Fcan't afford to pay back into a
OL,10,Fpension pot - something she says her
OL,11,Fhusband has never had to consider.
OL,13,FClair says: "Not paying into (the
OL,14,Fpension) myself means that if anything
OL,15,Fwere to happen in the future, I don't
OL,16,Fhave that financial stability".
OL,18,FThe pension gender gap exists
OL,19,Fglobally, and it's often a lot higher
OL,20,Fthan the wage gap:
