OL,3,C'Motherhood penalty' fuels pension
OL,4,Cgender gap crisis
OL,6,FShe told ITV News: "Women are living
OL,7,Flonger - they tend to be living on
OL,8,Ftheir own and they're living on less
OL,9,Fmoney.
OL,11,F"We're looking at how we can design
OL,12,Fpensions so that they work better for
OL,13,Fwomen who are coming through the
OL,14,Fsystem at the moment, but also make
OL,15,Fsure that the pensions that we do have
OL,16,Fallow people to live on them
OL,17,Fthroughout retirement."
